CuraLive Shadow Mode — Quick Setup Guide

For: All Team Members
Date: March 2026

════════════════════════════════════════════

WHAT IS SHADOW MODE?

Shadow Mode lets CuraLive silently sit inside any live webcast — Zoom, Teams,
Google Meet, or Webex — and collect intelligence in the background.

The client sees nothing different. The event runs as normal.
CuraLive quietly listens, transcribes, and analyses everything.

════════════════════════════════════════════

BEFORE THE EVENT — 3 THINGS TO CHECK

✅ 1. CuraLive is open and running on your computer
✅ 2. You have the meeting join link from the client or event coordinator
✅ 3. You have told the meeting host that a participant called
      "CuraLive Intelligence" will join and must be let in

That's all the preparation needed.

════════════════════════════════════════════

ON THE DAY — STEP BY STEP

STEP 1 — Open Shadow Mode

Go to CuraLive → Operator Platform Links → Shadow Mode
(or type /shadow-mode in the address bar)

─────────────────────────────────────────────

STEP 2 — Click "New Session"

Green button, top right corner of the screen.

─────────────────────────────────────────────

STEP 3 — Fill in 4 things

  Who is the client?     → Type the company name
                           Example: Anglo American Platinum

  What is the event?     → Type a short description
                           Example: Q4 2025 Earnings Call

  What type of event?    → Choose from the dropdown:
                           Earnings Call / AGM / Capital Markets Day /
                           CEO Town Hall / Board Meeting / Webcast / Other

  What platform?         → Choose: Zoom / Teams / Meet / Webex

  Paste the link         → Paste the meeting join URL
                           This is the same link sent to participants

─────────────────────────────────────────────

STEP 4 — Click "Start Shadow Intelligence"

The system will now send our intelligence bot into the meeting.

⏱ Wait 30 to 60 seconds.

The bot joins as "CuraLive Intelligence" in the participant list.
The session status on your screen will change to LIVE.

  ⚠ If the meeting has a waiting room, the host must click "Admit"
    for the CuraLive Intelligence participant. Make sure the host
    knows this before the event starts.

─────────────────────────────────────────────

STEP 5 — During the event

You can watch the live transcript appear on your screen in real time.
You do not need to do anything else while the event is running.

CuraLive is automatically:
  → Transcribing every word spoken
  → Scoring investor sentiment every few minutes
  → Scanning for compliance keywords
  → Saving everything to the database

─────────────────────────────────────────────

STEP 6 — End the session

When the event finishes, click the red "End Session" button.

CuraLive will then:
  → Remove the bot from the meeting
  → Process the full transcript
  → Save the intelligence records to the database
  → Show you a summary on screen

Done. ✅

════════════════════════════════════════════

WHAT IF SOMETHING GOES WRONG?

PROBLEM: Bot does not join after 60 seconds
FIX: Check the meeting link is correct and the meeting is live.
     Ask the host if there is a waiting room — they may need to admit the bot.

PROBLEM: Session shows "Failed"
FIX: The meeting link may be wrong or the meeting has not started yet.
     Click New Session and try again with the correct link.

PROBLEM: No transcript showing after the event
FIX: The bot may not have been admitted into the meeting.
     For Zoom, the account admin may need to allow third-party bots.
     Contact the development team if this happens more than once.

PROBLEM: Sentiment shows a dash (—) with no score
FIX: This is normal for very short events. Sentiment needs at least
     5 minutes of active speech to produce a reliable score.

════════════════════════════════════════════

AFTER THE EVENT — CHECK YOUR RESULTS

Go to: Tagged Metrics Dashboard (/tagged-metrics)

You will see 4 new records for the event:
  1. Sentiment score — how positively the event landed overall
  2. Engagement score — how active the conversation was
  3. Compliance risk score — any flagged language to review
  4. Session completion — confirmation everything was captured

════════════════════════════════════════════

GOOD TO KNOW

→ If you forget to click End Session, the bot leaves on its own:
     2 minutes after everyone leaves the meeting
    10 minutes if no one ever joined
    20 minutes if stuck in a waiting room

→ The bot does not speak, does not send messages, and does not
  interfere with the meeting in any way.

→ Run Shadow Mode on every Bastion webcast going forward.
  The more events you capture, the more valuable the data becomes.

════════════════════════════════════════════

QUICK REFERENCE CARD

  Before event   → Get the join link. Tell the host to admit "CuraLive Intelligence".
  Start          → Shadow Mode → New Session → Fill in details → Start Shadow Intelligence
  During event   → Leave it running. CuraLive handles everything automatically.
  After event    → Click End Session → Check Tagged Metrics Dashboard

